session.assistant:
**Root cause:** `erk-mcp` is missing from `[tool.uv.sources]` in `pyproject.toml`.

The workspace has 5 member packages (`erk`, `erk-dev`, `erk-mcp`, `erk-shared`, `erk-statusline`), but only 3 are declared in `[tool.uv.sources]`. Since `erk-mcp` isn't listed, `uv sync` doesn't treat it as a local workspace package and removes it along with all 47 of its transitive dependencies (fastmcp, mcp, starlette, uvicorn, etc.). Then something (likely the MCP server config or a cached venv) reinstalls them, creating the cycle.

**Fix:** Add one line to `pyproject.toml`:

```toml
[tool.uv.sources]
erk-dev = { workspace = true }
erk-mcp = { workspace = true }      # <-- add this
erk-shared = { workspace = true }
erk-statusline = { workspace = true }
```
